{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "V4 Brand Story LUT library. Two systems coexist for backwards compatibility:\n  • LEGACY (creative_legacy): 8 hand-graded .cube files keyed by id. Used when BRAND_STORY_LUT_SPEC_SYSTEM != 'true'.\n  • SPEC (creative): 22 genre-anchored declarative LUTs synthesized on demand by services/v4/LutSpecGenerator.js.\nResolution waterfall (PostProduction): per-model correction LUT → unified creative LUT (genre or legacy).",
    "strategy": "When the spec system is ON, BrandKitLutMatcher.matchByGenreAndMood() resolves a story's LUT by (1) genre → genre LUT pool, (2) mood-keyword overlap with story tone. Brand-vertical matching is deprecated on the spec side; brand identity flows to the generative pass (GenerativeLut.js) as a tonal trim layered on top of the genre grade.",
    "schema": {
      "spec_entry": "{ id, genre, is_default_for_genre?, look, mood_keywords[], reference_films[], spec: { lift[r,g,b], gamma[r,g,b], gain[r,g,b], saturation, shadow_tint[r,g,b], midtone_tint[r,g,b], highlight_tint[r,g,b] } }",
      "legacy_entry": "{ id, file, look, suits_brand_types[], mood_keywords[], hex_signature[], is_safe_fallback? }"
    },
    "updated": "2026-04-27"
  },

